From: sens@FASECON.ECON.NYU.EDU (Sunando Sen)
Subject: Re: Bootable floppy-based system...
Date: 30 Nov 93 23:02:02 GMT

In article <1993Nov30.200509.19765@rosevax.rosemount.com> grante@hydro.rosemount.com (Grant Edwards) writes:

>Well, libc.so is a little over 600K.  By the time you put the kernel
>(300K), libc.so (600K), a shell (220K), you run out of room on the
>floppy for any useful stuff like tar, cpio, a text editor, etc.
>
>Bummer.

  You need the `libc-lite.so' library, which you will have to compile from 
the libc source.  This is a `sparse file', so that although it is apparently 
600k in size, it actually takes up only a bit more than 200k.

Sunando Sen

