Subject: Re: Application Framework
Date: 30 Nov 1993 23:29:27 GMT

Peter P Chiu (ppc2@cec2.wustl.edu) wrote:

: is there an object oriented application framework for X windows out there?
: can someone please tell me where it is?

check tsx-11.mit.edu:/pub/linux/packages/oi/*
OI is the Parc Place Interface builder, which produces
openlook and motif like code in C++

OI is available for free for Linux and *BSD in binary form
thanks to Warner Losh and other great people at ParcPlace. 
OI is big $$$$$$ for SunOS Ultrix and HPUX, but free for Linux 
and *BSD. Thanks again Warner and other ParcPlace folks!

